- Place dirty dishes in the dishwasher and run it before you leave. 
- Leave used sheets and towels where they are.

welcome_guide.body: When leaving our office, turn right at the light towards CO-9 S/Summit Blvd. Follow CO-9 S for 10.7 miles to Boreas Pass Road in Breckenridge. Turn left onto Boreas Pass Road and in 0.7 miles turn left onto Bright Hope Circle. Take your first right onto Brooks Hill Drive, and your home will be on the right-hand side.

welcome_guide.title: Inventory/Starter Kits
welcome_guide.body:
You will find the home is stocked with all the basics:

- Ready-made beds and at least 1 bath towel, hand towel and wash cloth per guest
- Kitchen stocked with glasses, dishes, and utensils, as well as basic cookware
- The kitchen starter kit includes: hand soap, sponge, dish soap, dishwasher tabs, a roll of paper towels, and kitchen trash bags 
- Each bathroom is equipped with a starter kit which includes a hotel-style set of bath soap, shampoo, conditioner, and two rolls of toilet paper
- Laundry detergent 

The starter kits provided are complimentary and are meant to cover your needs before you get to the store to do your shopping. You may find supplies that have been left by other guests which you are welcome to use, but make sure to take a quick inventory before you shop to ensure you have everything you will need during your stay.

welcome_guide.title: Book your return visit direct with us and save!
welcome_guide.body: We love our repeat guests and can't wait for your return!  When you book through 'Channels' like AirBnb, booking.com or VRBO you're paying between 3-15% more than if you book directly through Beachcomber Vacation Homes. Click on this link to see future availability on this home or browse all of our homes *[here](https://www.airbnb.com)*.

welcome_guide.title: Accidental Damages
welcome_guide.body: Your rental agreement includes a security deposit protection plan. The home will be inspected after departure. Please make sure that you notify Bluewater of any damages prior to departure, otherwise, the security deposit protection is void and your credit card will be charged for the cost of repair/replacement. The most common damages include stains on towels, linens, and carpet. If damage is found to be excessive, or caused by negligence it will not be covered under the policy.

google.name: Blue Ridge Beer Hub
google.formatted_address: 21 East St, Waynesville, NC 28786, USA

reviews.text: I’ve found Mecca here in waynesville NC!!! Have lived here a year and am so mad I just now discovered this place.  My husband and I are beer snobs and our favorite thing is finding new and tasty craft beers.  We’ve had people bring us  St. Bernardus beer from Florida when visiting because we had not found it here.   And then— we find Mecca. Fantastic selection of beers even we haven’t heard of.  We will be frequent patrons... so excited!

Awesome little find! We were searching for Dragon's Milk beer and found what we were looking for here. We called ahead and they set aside the beers for us! Really awesome spot with friendly and very helpful staff. A wide wide selection of beers, local and other locations. Really nice gift options t-shirts, key chains, pint glass leather sleeve, key chains, stickers, candy, and much more. Cannot wait to make another trip to this awesome spot in the gorgeous town of Waynesville!
Great location, selection and prices. Cool little tasting bar also!

Great bottle shop.  I visited from out of state and the worker walked me around the whole store with tons of great local beer suggestions for things I cannot readily buy where I live.  Very friendly and knowledgeable staff and great selection.
So many wonderful beers to choose from.  The owner was very nice and knowledgeable as well.  I was very impressed with the prices also.

google.name: Junaluska Gifts & Grounds
google.formatted_address: 710 N Lakeshore Dr, Lake Junaluska, NC 28745, USA

reviews.text: Nice gift shop. Great place to grab a coffee or ice cream.

As far as I'm concern the lake is the gem of Haywood County. I visit often and during summer yes stop and get some ice cream and set on the porch. Being local I've attended many events there. Its a beautiful place great place to walk the trails boat, fish, swim in the pool plus we really enjoy the resturants. Just a great place to spend time. Blessed every time I go

The pandemic has me stressed. My coffee consumption had stopped. But the first cup of coffee in months came from here. Oh so good it was. Nice and dark and great flavor without after taste. God bless them.
Great customer service to match great surroundings  :)
Great selection of food and drinks for a small cafe and the gift shop it's in is packed full of great items, most of which are locally made.

google.name: Somatic Healing Clinic
google.formatted_address: 130 Miller St, Waynesville, NC 28786, USA

reviews.text: I had my first visit today and DJ was phenomenal. Very knowledgeable and took the time to address my health needs. The atmosphere is great. It is calm and relaxing if you are looking to just decompress.  I look forward to my next visit and would highly recommend to others.
Ashley and DJ both are amazing... I  use Ashley and my husband uses DJ and they both do a great job. I love the environment of this place as well.  Very quiet and relaxing....
Ashley provided an excellent deep tissue massage and was very knowledgeable.  The space is beautiful and relaxing.  Highly recommend.
Great massage with Ashley!  Warm surroundings and friendly staff.
Don't know do matenance on roof real nice looking place would be a nice place to sit and enjoy a beer or wine

google.name: Twigs & Leaves Gallery
google.formatted_address: 98 N Main St, Waynesville, NC 28786, USA

reviews.text: This is a phenomenal gallery with many very talented artists represented.  Beautiful pottery, glass, wood, and many other gift ideas.  A must see if you are in the area.

One of my most favorite shops anywhere! I visit anytime I'm in Waynesville. The shop carries a fascinating mix of paintings, pottery, jewelry, crafted wooden pieces, textile art, and more. It's a special place.
Very helpful and knowledgeable about the jewelry in the store from local artists/jewelers.
Love this place, awesome hard to find items. Thanks

We love this place.   It is full of hand crafted goods. They have  pottery,  furniture, paintings,  jewelry and more.   If you are  in the area and like hand crafted art,  do yourself a favor and stop by.

google.name: Go Grocery Outlet
google.formatted_address: 257 Waynesville Plaza, Waynesville, NC 28786, USA

reviews.text: I love this place. I can get a buggy full of groceries for less than $100. I went for the 10lb roll of ground beef for $1.59 a lb.
Great place to find good deals, great first stop for groceries
Make sure you check the expiration dates! This is why everything is cheaper bc most of it is expired. Check the meat thoroughly too, a lot had mold growing!
Very low prices. Good pork and chicken. Fair variety of name brands. Usually a moderate line at checkout.
Great prices, friendly staff, quality products.

google.name: Ferrara Pizza & Pasta
google.formatted_address: 243 Paragon Pkwy #11A, Clyde, NC 28721, USA

reviews.text: Before the pandemic we ate at Ferrara’s all the time. Now, at least 1-2 times a month we still pick up dinner. I often use the Slice app to order our food. Our kids love their pizza. I like the eggplant Stromboli. My husband always gets the Alfredo. The people who work there are always friendly. Highly recommend.

Would recommend. The food was great. Everything had so much flavor and their bread is so soft and just great. The bathrooms were really clean. And everyone working was very nice and on top of things. Definitely a place to go!
The food and service were beyond my expectations. We really enjoyed the ambience of this place. Superb spot to take my family out for lunch.
Had a fantastic experience in this spot with my kid. The food arrives fast and the service is just great. Prices are reasonable.
Just moved here from Nashville looking for a really good pizza! Definitely found it here. Will be back for sure!! Very friendly staff and fresh hot pizza!!!

google.name: Mast General Store Waynesville, NC
google.formatted_address: 63 N Main St, Waynesville, NC 28786, USA

reviews.text: Very great service! It was my first time visiting, I'm from Florida and I highly recommend this place to anyone who wants to go shop in a cute little store downtown. Also  your employee Keaton was very friendly and a lot of fun! We played football with the hackey sack! PS I didn't break anything so no worries and he was doing his job the whole time.

First time at this location.  It’s stocked like each of the other stores.  Great merchandise! Competitive prices. Friendly and informative staff.  Quaint location with charm of its own. Pet friendly!  Kid friendly.
The Mast has fantastic outdoor brands and gear. Their prices are MSRP, but the service is great. They also often have sales which alleviate the otherwise steep prices. I really like this store!

Very good store to get your hiking essentials that you forgot to pack and are sitting on your dining room table. Even though they are located in Gatlinberg NOC is not gimmicky at all. They sell the major players in hiking/backpacking gear.
Great service. Great selection. Great little town. Support local businesses.

google.name: HART Theatre
google.formatted_address: 250 Pigeon St, Waynesville, NC 28786, USA

reviews.text: The theater was run wonderfully. The show was fantastic. Will Be Back!
This place is amazing Sheele is so cool
Very professional very courteous very clean

Wonderful, attended a fund raiser for Pathways (a homeless rehabilitation center in Waynesville, NC) a annual fund raiser called, "Empty Bowl".  There was great music entertainment and tasty cups of soups sponsored by local restaurants as well as reasonable raffle tickets available in Hope's of winning some awesome prizes...I certainly hope I am able to attend next year's event!!!

I have been wanting to visit the Hart for a while. We decided to give it a try for the production of Oliver. What a treat. The inside of the theater alone was beautiful. Big enough to not feel crowded, but small enough to feel intimate. I will be visiting again!

google.name: Corneille Bryan native garden
google.formatted_address: 194 Stuart Cir, Lake Junaluska, NC 28745, USA

reviews.text: Nice, quaint , peaceful place. Plants marked very well.  Beautiful!

Visited in the fall and everything was mostly dying but it's still a beautiful and unique thing to see. There's a small creek running through and plenty of places to sit. The sound of the creek and nature is so relaxing.

Nice hideaway gardens between three side streets. My wife absolutely loved the walk. The garden paths are nicely kept, and many of the plants have labels saying what each is. The overall beauty of the flowers, trees, etc. are worth the time, and the price can't be beaten. We went on a warm day, and the shade from the trees reduced the heat very nicely.
Perfect compact but beautiful garden spot.
We discovered this public garden by chance. The director was there cleaning up the grounds. Very charming and more than 500 native plants.

recommendations.name: Asheville Regional Airport
recommendations.address: 61 Terminal Dr #1, Fletcher, NC 28732, United States

google.name: Asheville Regional Airport
google.formatted_address: 61 Terminal Dr #1, Fletcher, NC 28732, USA

reviews.text: Driving from northern Virginia to Western North Carolina, the motor blew in my car. My wife and I had to make it home after the holiday. For the same price of renting a car and fuel, we were able to get a last minute flight from Avl to Iad. That puts us one exit away from our home. Its a cute, nice airport. The staff are very helpful. The jet was small, but very comfy. We flew United and made it home in an hr and a half for less than 600 for the both of us. That was purchased 3hrs before the flight. We will now fly here to visit family. I never knew there were regular flights from close to home to close to family for very low price, especially if booked in advance. We will now fly in and out of here every few months. Such a great experience

I was very pleased. Nice friendly staff. They were very helpful to my mom who needed wheelchair assistant. They made she she got on the plane on time and took really good care of her medical device. Thank you all so much.
Very convenient airport. Close to interstate exit, parking close to terminal. Minimal walking and getting luggage on return was quick.  Small tasteful food court.
We had no wait and were seated with coffee quickly. Our waiter was attentive and efficient. The food was wonderful and exactly as we ordered it.

Let me start by saying that the only reason we booked with this airport is because the flights were the earlier than Knoxville. This was all in vain since the scheduling is so poor with this airport. The departing and returning flights were both over 45 minutes late. Then, when we returned home we were stuck on the taxiway due to a plane being in the way since they were also late. We were stuck for over 30 minutes. We will never, ever fly out of this airport again if we don’t have to. The scheduling is poor and unreliable, and the facilities are cramped. McGee-Tyson is far superior and reliable.

google.name: Burger King
google.formatted_address: 575 Russ Ave, Waynesville, NC 28786, USA

reviews.text:
EDITED FOR 5☆ REVIEW: My husband and I decoded to be bold and eat in for the first time since the pandemic started and we were incredibly impressed by the sanitation routines and thoroughness of the cleaning done by the staff.

OLD 4☆REVIEW: Always fast service and accurate orders. Bathrooms and dining room are generally reasonably clean, but there have been many visits where the restaurant was mostly empty and yet there was not a single clean table to be found. That said, we certainly arent above cleaning up here and there and understand that just because it doesnt look busy at the moment, doesn't mean its not- so four stars! We will happily be back for a fast, easy meal.
This is the best Burger King I probably ever been to. All the staff are very friendly as well and we had the freshest sandwiches that I've ever had at any Burger King.
They used to be good. They can't get a simple order correct anymore. Good job for getting half of a $30 order you have lost my business and good day
Spicy chicken was like jerky. Crazy dry holy jeez. I’ve had it at a bunch of other locations and they’ve been great every time.
The Whooper is the best. All impressed that masks were worn

Dirty and poor quality. What else do you expect from a Sub shop inside a gas station? They used stale crusty bread for my sub, and were out of many things. (Cheese, meats, bread and toppings.) Very disappointed. :(

reviews.text: Did an amazing job getting me the vaccinate and caring for my anxiety of needles
Website is too slow and stops in the middle of downloading coupons.  Store staff is very friendly and helpful.  Pharmacy staff are also helpful and willing to answer any questions about my meds.

One of my favorite places to shop! Have a variety of products no matter what you are looking for. If you guys ever get Mberry please let me know! Thanks :)

I tried to pick up my meds and they told me I wasn't who I said I was and made me spend 2 days trying to find obscure insurance information, not before telling me to apply for Medicaid because they couldn't believe I had tricare dependent coverage.

reviews.text: Attention don’t take silverware off table when somebody gone to bathroom and clean the table especially when I’ve not put my napkin in plate with the silverware drink was gone does that’s happen with everybody that comes in and decides to use the bathroom and come back to clean table it just takes look of the eyes to observe and decide are they gone or are they in bathroom but then again by look at food on the bar I understand fully why they was in bathroom in first place food was not best they could do  breakfast is worth going for but lunch on other hand needs improve especially doing the trying times cause that’s  when restaurants need to shine not disappoint the most important people the customer

It was pretty good but it just don't have the atmosphere the old Shoney's had. Also it doesn't matter where you go anymore, everybody that owns a restaurant thinks they have to have a bar. I wouldn't be surprised if McDonald's eventually has one. Yes I need a chicken mcnugget happy meal and a Coors for my drink.
To long to get food 😩 my bake 🥔 was cold 🥶 the brought fries 🍟 they were cold 🥶 hamburger 🍔 was good service was a little slow 🐌 don't think ill be back

Love this place, awesome hard to find items. Thanks

google.name: Therapeutic Massage & Wellness Spa llc
google.formatted_address: 288 N Haywood St, Waynesville, NC 28786, USA

reviews.text: The experience was amazing. We arrived 10 minutes early for a couples massage and they took us right back. Everything was very clean and professional. Layla did an incredible job of communicating and guiding me through the whole experience. Layla’s work on a deep tissue massage was amazing. I left feeling invigorated and refreshed. I definitely will be going back.

My wife and I had a couples pregnancy massage, they were kind and gentle with my wife and left her feeling relaxed and beautiful. I too had a great experience with a deep tissue massage. Highly recommend.

Really well-managed, clean and lovely spa experience. The staff - especially Rhonda and Dana - were kind, professional and accommodating. This location offers a ton of different spa and wellness services and the prices are amazing. Highly recommend.

On my very first visit Rhonda helped me out by giving me a deep therapeutic massage. She really worked the knots out in my back and gave a lot of pressure that I needed to be able to get those spots taken care of. Thank you so much Rhonda! I look forward to visiting again real soon. So glad to have them here in Waynesville!
I would absolutely recommend! Rhonda was amazing! So professional and thorough. Helped my back pain tremendously!

google.name: World Methodist Museum
google.formatted_address: 575 N Lakeshore Dr, Lake Junaluska, NC 28745, USA

reviews.text: Very nice museum with some interesting exhibit items. Most of it is Methodist centered with a few Holy Land items. The ladies who host the museum are precious and very accommodating. I only took off a star because it is a small museum and very targeted in it's displays.
Sat outside on a bench enjoying the lake.
Very informative! There is a short video at the beginning about what you will see, but otherwise the tour is self guided.
A treasure trove of information about the Methodist Church and it's earliest days in the United States.
Wonderful informative museum.  Our Docent guide Ashley was so nice and informative. Great exhibits on Methodist beginnings along with many unique surprises!

google.name: Blue Rooster Southern Grill
google.formatted_address: 207 Paragon Pkwy, Clyde, NC 28721, USA

reviews.text: We stopped in on Thursday traveling south this past week and were pleasantly surprised how good the food was! Our only disappointment is that they were not open on Sunday so we could visit again!   Everything was so good!  The service, the sweet tea, the rolls, tomato bisque soup (I almost ordered a to go serving, it was so good!), taco salad, chicken salad, Caroline burger and OH My Goodness the coconut cake was heavenly!!!  Top of our list of places to stop!!
The food is fabulous. Huge portions, and a great value. Service is friendly and fast.  If I'm ever in Waynesville I'll be sure to carve out a time to visit again.

The service and the food are ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️. Very cozy and clean restaurant. I 100% recommend this place. Chelsey S. was our waitress. She is amazing, sweet and helpful. The grilled chicken was delicious. Even the rolls tasted freshly made. If we ever come back to North Caroline we will try to stop by again.
The food is divine. The service is fantastic.  It's a good thing I don't live in Waynesville because I'd have to eat here every day.
Good food, friendly staff. Very attentive server. Prices are on the high side.  $12 for a burger and fries.  I've lived here for over 30 years, it's just too high for the area.

google.formatted_address: 35 Bridge St, Waynesville, NC 28786, USA

reviews.text: This company sells some of the best tasting natural sodas I’ve had. The only thing I would add is maybe do one sugar free for people that would love to enjoy your soda without a sugar rush.

We love it! We first tasted it at Sierra Nevada Brewery Company and loved its original taste and freshness! Can’t wait to return to NC...we will stop by your soda company to buy some more. Best of luck!!!

I love this place! I'm hooked on the Strawberry Rhubarb. If I remember correctly, it was made with strawberries from Waynesville, and Rhubarb from Robbinsville. Craft soda at it's best! These guys have a bright future and if you ever come across them, make sure to pick up a soda! Definitely worth trying if you haven't yet. Cool staff, and a nice new location.
Really like these sodas! I grab one whenever I see them sold. Just tried the strawberry rhubarb and it was delicious and refreshing.
Waynesville Soda is the best! We live 1.5 hrs away and making the trip for a case or two is well worth it.

Transferred Rx from Walmart for convenience and 9 times out of 10, they aren't open when they say they will be.
Wonderful pharmacy with an amazing staff!
Great locally owned small businesses. Staff is very helpful, friendly, & fast. Always a pleasure to walk in the store.

google.name: Lambuth Inn
google.formatted_address: 55 Lambuth Dr, Lake Junaluska, NC 28745, USA

reviews.text:
Lambeth Inn was the site for Covid vaccine drive thru clinic. The Lake is always a great community partner and supporter.
Have visited there several times. Beautiful historic facility.
Nice views. Peaceful place
Beautiful hotel. Very clean. Nice size rooms.

We stayed here for two days and nights and this hotel was perfect. Nothing was out of place and the view was beautiful. The staff were friendly and accommodating and went above and beyond for us. The beds were the most comfortable beds we've ever slept on. Despite how convenient access to the highway is, there was no noise whatsoever and we got some much needed peace and quiet. I would highly recommend The Lambuth Inn to anyone traveling in this area.

DO NOT STAY AT THIS HOTEL!
I have never left a review bad or good for any business I have used. So to get me to leave a review it would have to be really good or really bad. In this case REALLY BAD   We arrived at 3am. The man checking us in was clueless it took an hour to check in. My wife noticed there was a note on the desk that said a women came down to the desk and brought BED BUGS from her room. I was scared at this point to check in but we had just drove 6 hours in the car and it was Valentine’s Day and our anniversary so we proceeded to the room. We asked for a nice room we were told we had a lake view.  Which I guess we did if you stuck you head out the window and could look around the building but mostly they stuck us in a back corner. We left the room in good order we had drank a 6 pack of beer and we left the empty bottles in the trash can. We knew it was a Christian hotel but there was nothing that said you couldn’t drink a beer. We left a $10 tip for the maid and left.  We were told the room was $149 per night. When I received my credit card statement I had three separate charges on my card one for $149 one for $464.19 and another for $292.37. There explication was there were beer bottles in the room. Thank God for American Express I won’t be paying this bill. And the manager I spoke to about this was nasty. DO NOT STAY AT THIS HOTEL!!

reviews.text: So we were not staying here, but just stopped by for a run on the trail around the lake.  Beautiful campus.  Definitely stop by at the top of the hour to hear their beautiful chimes.  Decent path around the lake, although narrow in places.  People seem to think they are the only ones there, as they seem surprised when we call 'on your left' as we pass.  Loved the bridges and one lane bridge.  Just such a nice place to get some miles in.  Park near the acquatic center.

Family oriented. Love the mountains. Charming homes dotted through this community. Fun shopping eating and folksy area Relaxed area. Water activities are available. Welcoming to all Christian denominations. Retreats and gatherings. You get to meet folks from other churches. Comfortable accommodations and dining. I loved visiting and staying at the Lambuth Inn on and up hill from lake.
What a great place for running or walking around the lake . 4miles on big loop and 2 on short . Found the to bistro has great food Thursday-Sunday .
Fantastic stay, highly recommend.  Clean, comfy and views of the lake are incredible.  Mark is first class; a great representative of your company!  Will definitely be back.  Gail and Morse
AV services by Riley Rowland (a failed filmmaker) are terrible

reviews.text: I've come here every summer since I was 10. The course is still the same. Gets a lot of play but stays in good shape. Great views.
Few ruff gravel cart path. Green just aerated, everything else fantastic.

Worst golf course in Western North Carolina. The service is terrible, and the staff at the front is always rude. There’s a lady that works at this course who has the personality of a rock. Rates are deceiving and they actually overcharge.

Great course in excellent condition. Friendly staff with beautiful scenery. Harrahs Cherokee casino is about 30 minutes away so definitely give this a stop on your trip...unless your gambling is bad then just stay near the golf course Lol Good luck!
This was the first time I had played  this course. The greens are in amazing good shape and the course requires a lot of special shots. I will definitely be back!

reviews.text: Generally prices are a little higher than their local competitors. However their weekly deals do make it worth the visit.

I love shopping at Publix! The employees are so nice and helpful starting at the front of the store. They wipe the entire shopping cart for each customer as you walk in. The store is always very clean and orderly. Shopping the sales and using coupons, Publix is not any more expensive than other grocery stores.
Great customer service!

Worst deli experience at a Publix in my life. Ordered subs online and they didn’t make the order, or call me, to ask what bread I’d like since they were out of what I ordered.  Also ordered 1/2 lb of sliced cheese that WAS ready for pickup. As I checked out I noticed they charged me for 1 lb. I weighed it at home and it was 1/2lb. I didn’t stop to complain because my warm sub was for someone waiting in my car for 30 minutes already, due to the bread issue.
I love $5 sushi Wednesday. What a treat! It's delicious and doesn't break my budget

google.formatted_address: 297 Paragon Pkwy, Clyde, NC 28721, USA

reviews.text: They were really on top of things in having to deal with dinner rush. Everything is take-out now. The cashier was extremely busy between getting phone orders and counter orders. She was still very friendly. Food is amazing.  Good ingredients. Great flavor. Traditional cuisine.

My wife has me get take out from here 2-3 times a month. We get the Pad Thai with no noodles and put it over Spaghetti squash now but previously we got it with noodles and all. They are very accommodating, in that they have now issues with our usual order. My son gets the pan fried dumplings and says they are the best here. I like spicy wife waivers but she says the medium is perfect spice for her.

Just wanted to leave a quick review for my order I had last weekend. Stayed at in AirBnB in Clyde, and had no idea what was around. Decided to wait inside and place an order on the spot even though the inside seemed busy, and I ended up waiting less than expected with how swamped they looked. The staff was generous and very attentive with making sure we got our order out on time. If you were all in Greensboro, I'd be going here more often than I should. I'll visit here again if I'm ever back in town!
I stopped while traveling, and I couldn't be happier. The prices are reasonable and the ingredients seem to be good quality. Nothing is greasy. Love it.
Amazingly wonderful food!! Decent price. Great employees..and hard working. Worth every penny plus some!! One of our favorite restaurants around!!!

reviews.text: Very clean and well manicured. Never too crowded.

The people behind the counter are the rudest people I’ve ever met in my entire life. I’ll never be back there. I think the ugly blonde woman behind the counters name was Tamara. If she hates her job that much she needs to quit. I’ll be telling everyone I know what a joke the Rec center is.

My first time here was amazing! So amazing I wanted to bring my family here yet it's still great but I happen to come across an older women here who works at the front desk who I found rude and hateful, you know I understand covid 19 is serious to others but you would think staff at work places could be a lot nicer about it this old women who works here could have approached me better with wearing a mask in the lobby and answer my question instead of ignoring my question she was like YOU NEED TO HAVE A MASK ON IN THE LOBBY. I SAID SORRY and I would get it but once again asked my question one yet she ignored me and hatefully said again and again You NEED TO HAVE A MASK ON IN THE LOBBY until finally I just had to walk away. I will come back but in Hope's this old hatefully woman will not be here and fyi to her if your so afraid of the virus stay at home!

Very grumpy front desk help!  Went   in to ask a few questions and the lady immediately took an attitude with us.  She responded to anything we asked as if we had been arguing with her but we hadn’t been. I don’t know if perhaps they get a lot of nasty people that they have to deal with and they just assume everyone is like that but. We won’t be going back!

Absolutely love this park. It's not too crowded and everyone is very polite.  I live in Asheville and it's a 40 minute drive,  but worth it because the parks in Asheville are overly crowded. I'll definitely be going back.

Awesome business with a great owner. Everyone should check it out. No telling what you will find.
Staff is wonderful and welcoming.  Great mix of vintage and antique items. I bring friends here.
Super super sweet people! They have a magnitude of fabulous items! A must see!
Very helpful

google.name: Lakeside Bistro at Lake Junaluska
google.formatted_address: 689 N Lakeshore Dr, Lake Junaluska, NC 28745, USA

reviews.text:
Hello,

Great place!! What a way to spend my first night in the mountains of western NC.

I decided to veer off the road , on my way to Maggie Valley, to see Lake Junaluska,  for a bite to eat and was most pleasantly surprised by this beautiful Lakeside town.

This is my first time here , and I googled for outside dining in Lake Junaluska, and found the bistro Lakeside at the Terrace.

The outside dining is on the third floor, and has the most spectacular view of the lake and the sunset.

Everyone at the bistro went out of their way to make sure I had a fabulous experience.it was a chilly night but they had heaters and it was perfect.

I started with a small Caesar salad,  which had
to be one of the best Caesar salad’s I’ve ever had !

Everything is made from scratch, and I ordered  the buttermilk chicken with the Brussels sprouts, and the macaroni and cheese .👍👍👍
So fantastic.

Just a note, there is no alcohol served here yet,  but if you have your own wine or beer, you can bring it in. I happened  to have a bottle of wine with me so that worked out quite well.

I also splurged, and had dessert which was the fresh berry crisp. Yummy.

Everything was delicious , and so much food!!

I want to say thank you to Chef Sam, my server Megan, and also the host, Daniel . As I’m  on a  vacation, Chef Sam who is a native , came out to talk with me about the area and where to go. He was so helpful!
Thank you , Chef Sam!

The downstairs lobby level has a very large fireplace and beautiful floor to ceiling  windows overlooking the lake, and rugged rustic wood, and  glass and stone walls.

Everything was very beautiful and I am glad I ventured off my path to find this place.👏👏

Thank you!

Jennifer from Deerfield Beach, Florida

Just had a lovely impromptu late lunch at The Bistro.  The views are amazing! Our server Javan was attentive and professional so we felt very well taken care of! I must admit, I grew up in the area and had very little experience with dining at Lake Junaluska but it seems the new owners/management have breathed new life into the place! I had a lovely perfectly dressed salad and a cup of the soup, my mother had the artichoke spinach dip as her meal... oh my!! Absolutely heavenly! We were so full, we had to order our desserts to go!! I will definitely be back and I highly recommend that if you're in the area to stop in. This is a gem of a dining experience with relaxing views of the lake.

Enjoyed a lovely meal at the Lakeside Bistro last night. Javan was our server and did an exceptional job taking care of us. The views were amazing and the food was delicious! My husband says the banana pudding is the best he's ever had! Will definitely visit again when we take our next vacation to Maggie Valley!

First time visiting The Lakeside Bistro.  Had the Buttermilk fried chicken ,with Brussel sprouts.  Very good. Also had the Spinach and Artichoke dip. Came out hot with the most awesome chips. Maggie was a great waitress and Andy , the Manager  came out and checked on us. Please stop by and check this place out. Lunch and dinner are served.

The staff were extremely friendly. We were seated at a table by the window with a great view of the lake but then decided to get it to go so we could watch the snow in our cabin. We ordered 1 of each pizza & the cornbread. The pizza is delicious. The cornbread is good but I like it more moist.

Stopped in at this kitchen shop today and fell in love with it.  Purchased a hanging pot rack for my daughter along with many other things.  I went in to get a tube pan and left with 4 bags of goodies.  The staff was super friendly and helpful, even made suggestions for the best lunch places.  If you are in Waynesville don't miss going in this shop!
A lot of stuff here.  Wife loved it.
This is a very well stocked shop and they are always helpful and friendly. A must visit for  gifts and you own kitchen.

Lovely shop and employees. We are now permanent residents of Waynesville and always stop in to see new products, creative displays and say hello. If you're in town visiting make every attempt to stop in....worth the stop.
